This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The country programme is effectively designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children.

title.narrative: Cross Sectoral

description.narrative: New partnerships were established which expanded Cross-sectoral/PME section significantly with more funds and staff for 2022 and 2023. The design of the new Convergence Programme, a multi-sectoral programming in two districts, was completed including comprehensive baseline assessment and consultations. UNICEF PNG increased its investment in building evidence for social policies for children with the completion of two evaluations and two major research initiatives and eleven evidence generation initiatives ongoing. ;Also, a number of initiatives strengthened programming – the completion of the PSEA/CS action plan, the field monitoring SOP, Third party monitoring guidance note, and AAP action plan drafted. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/01/2022
